 \end{array}
 $$

Therefore, the quotient is $\boxed{x^5 - x^4 + x^3 - x^2 + x - 1}$.

To find the remainder when $x^5 + x^4 + x^3 + x^2 + x$ is divided by $x^3 - 4x$, we can use polynomial long division.  

Performing the division, we get:

 $$
 \begin{array}{c|ccccc}
 \multicolumn{2}{r}{x^2} & + & 5x & + & 20 \\
 \cline{2-6}
 x^3 - 4x & x^5 & + & x^4 & + & x^3 & + & x^2 & + & x \\
 \multicolumn{2}{r}{x^5} & - & 4x^3 & & & & & & \\
