$$
R(-\theta) = \begin{bmatrix}
\cos (-\theta) & -\sin (-\theta) \\
\sin (-\theta) & \cos (-\theta)
\end{bmatrix}
$$

For a 45° clockwise rotation, θ = -45°.  We know that cos(-45°) = √2 / 2 and sin(-45°) = -√2 / 2.  Substituting these values, we get:

$$
R(-45°) = \boxed{\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} & \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \\
-\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} & \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}
\end{bmatrix}}
$$

